        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 4:22PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Haskell, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Haskell around 425 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
